provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/functools.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/functools.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: functools.lru_cache decorated function attributes — functools._lru_cache_wrapper.__name__=='_lru_cache_wrapper' (len=18); functools._lru_cache_wrapper.__module__=='functools'; functools.singledispatch.__class__.__name__=='function'; functools.singledispatchmethod.__name__=='singledispatchmethod' (len=20); functools.singledispatchmethod.__module__=='functools'; functools.singledispatchmethod.__mro__.__len__()==2."
    - "functools._lru_cache_wrapper.__name__ == '_lru_cache_wrapper' — _lru_cache_wrapper is the C extension type that wraps a function decorated by lru_cache; it stores the cache and exposes cache_info() and cache_clear(); its __name__ is '_lru_cache_wrapper', 18 characters. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "functools._lru_cache_wrapper.__module__ == 'functools' — _lru_cache_wrapper is exposed via the functools module (implemented in _functoolsmodule.c); its __module__ is 'functools'. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "functools.singledispatch.__class__.__name__ == 'function' — singledispatch is a Python decorator function defined in Lib/functools.py; its __class__.__name__ is 'function'. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "functools.singledispatchmethod.__name__ == 'singledispatchmethod' — singledispatchmethod is a Python descriptor class in Lib/functools.py that provides singledispatch support for methods; its __name__ is 'singledispatchmethod', 20 characters (the longest name among functools public names in this spec). Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "functools.singledispatchmethod.__module__ == 'functools' — singledispatchmethod is defined in Lib/functools.py; its __module__ is 'functools'. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "functools.singledispatchmethod.__mro__.__len__() == 2 — singledispatchmethod is a Python class inheriting directly from object; its MRO is (singledispatchmethod, object), a tuple of length 2. Verified with Python 3.14.3."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

